Mission.Author: KingRaptor
Mission.Description: Ada engages in a deadly race with the Valhallans to find the modern-day lost city, the Central Consciousness.
Mission.Name: Sunrise Episode 4C - A Link to the Past

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = Spring.GetAllUnits() for i=1,#units do Spring.SetUnitAlwaysVisible(units[i], true) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Alright. Our Norse friends already have a considerable presence here; we'll need to move fast if we want to save the settlement.
The artefact's in the center of the island, surrounded by what defenses the villagers could muster. We need to secure whatever is inside its data core before they do.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local units = Spring.GetAllUnits() for i=1,#units do Spring.SetUnitAlwaysVisible(units[i], false) end
Spring.SetTeamResource(0,"m",370) Spring.SetTeamResource(0,"e",240) Spring.SetTeamResource(1,"m",370) Spring.SetTeamResource(1,"e",575) Spring.SetTeamResource(2,"m",490) Spring.SetTeamResource(2,"e",775) Spring.SetTeamResource(3,"m",20) Spring.SetTeamResource(3,"e",50)
GG.CAI.SuspendAI(1, false) GG.CAI.SuspendAI(2, false)

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: The artefact's data core contains information the Valhallans want. Whatever it is, we can't let them have it.
TriggerLogic.Title: Secure the Artefact

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: By the way, Sophia. What does "Norse" mean?
Ancient Terran mythology. We can read about it together once we've resolved the situation before us.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Incoming kinetic strike! Ada, get away from the artefact!

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Odin") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SpawnCEG("gate", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_out", x, y, z) Spring.PlaySoundFile("sounds/misc/teleport.wav", 2.0, x, y, z, nil, nil, nil, "sfx") Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true)
--Spring.KillTeam(2)

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: So be it.
What is it you want with the artefact?
We seek Folkvangr, lost home of the Einherjar.
Folkvangr?
You know it as the Central Consciousness. With its billions of minds bound to our cause, we will cleanse the stars once more.
Not if I have anything to say about it. You want the datacore, pry it from my smouldering wreckage!
Do your worst. We expect no less.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SpawnCEG("gate", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_out", x, y, z) Spring.PlaySoundFile("sounds/misc/teleport.wav", 2.0, x, y, z, nil, nil, nil, "sfx") Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true)
--Spring.KillTeam(2)

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: I pulled you out just in time, Ada. Please be more careful - we can't afford to lose the command unit's firepower.
We're facing some nasty opposition here. Use of the Spectre sniper walker is warranted.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
The Spectre fires an energy rifle with a lethal punch matched only by its long reload time over medium-long distances. It is the only unit that can remain cloaked while firing.
Spectres are easily found and killed by large groups of small, light units running sweep patterns over likely positions.
Maces are really nasty customers in a sword fight. Try picking them off from a distance, if possible.
Scalpels inflict a lot of frontloaded damage but also take a long time to reload. Try using cheap units to waste their shots and then swarm them under.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Use of area shields might help strengthen our defenses around the artefact.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
The Aegis (static) and Aspis (mobile) area shields cover a wider area than personal shields and have a greater capacity, but require energy to charge up. They are useful for defending against artillery bombardment (assuming it isn't too heavy) and other medium-to-long range units.
The static and mobile forms are freely interchangable by morphing (although the static-to-mobile morph costs resources).

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: It appears the settlement uses geothermal power for most of its energy needs. We could do the same.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
Geothermal Powerplants provide a good amount of energy at an affordable price, but can only be built on steam vents. These are indicated by the smoke coming out of the ground and highlighted in economy view (F4).
Geothermal plants explode violently when destroyed, so don't build things next to them.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Remember that you can activate your special weapon with the 'D' key (default). It can really ruin an enemy formation's day.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: Some units have a special weapon, which can be activated with the D key (by default). These weapons have a long reload time, but can be very effective in the right situation.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.STOP, {}, 0) local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Odin") if unitID then GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.STOP, {}, 0) end

TriggerLogic.Message: Excellent. Folkvangr will soon be ours.
Damn it! Is there nothing we can do now?

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.STOP, {}, 0) local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Odin") if unitID then GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.STOP, {}, 0) end

TriggerLogic.Message: There we go. Datacore downloaded and purged. Valhallan units are withdrawing from the planetary surface.
It seems our work here is done. Let's go.
